headline: GD Q4 Deep Dive: Orders Surge, Supply Chain and Margin Pressures Persist
summary: Aerospace and defense company General Dynamics (NYSE:GD) reported Q4 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 7.8% year on year to $14.38 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.17 per share was 1.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
